text: The fascinating thing about these kind of movies is that they try to showcase the human condition--all the little quirks and things that may seem trivial or everyday but account for so much for what it means to be alive. Sometimes it takes a different mood to enjoy a movie like this, as opposed to the usual action or comedy flicks.  Anyway, I have a love of philosophy which comes from my fascination with being human and all the things we have accomplished throughout our short existence. I recently talked about our perceptions of what is right and wrong and how it plays into our progress overall (human rights, racism, LGBT, double standards, etc). Check it out, I promise not to let you down. The only way for me to improve is to encounter new minds and walks of life, so bring me your experiences and knowledge! Good day to you all :) Let's learn from one another.

text: Nice suburban house, all white cast, white people problems... why should i care? This movie has been done to death before, some better, some worse, but really? This is supposed to be an uplifting story about life, family and faith? Sorry, in real life, some people sitting alone in their room, drinking themselves to death, unable to communicate with other people, not even their own family. There's no quirky, hilarity that ensues, there's darkness and depression. Yet here we are, looking at these... people... whose sole problem is "my wife cheated on me", a relative died and "putting a baby in a woman". Are you kidding me? All ranting aside, this looks like your typical formulaic family comedy, though the cast might help to rise this above mediocrity.
